main event: A large, bright, elliptical object was observed over Lodi, New Jersey for several minutes on the evening of April 14, 1965. The object appeared to be hovering and maneuvering at a low altitude.
interesting points: The object was described as a large, bright, elliptical shape.
The object was observed for approximately 11 minutes.
The object appeared to be hovering and maneuvering at a low altitude.
The witness sent a request for additional information about the incident to the Air Technical Intelligence Center (ATIC).
Another page of the report describes an observation of a round, white object that disappeared going south, lasting around 30 seconds.
